definitions.def: Bus for public transportation in DR.
definitions.ex: Si tú quieres ir pa' allá, tú tiene' que coger una guagua.
definitions.gs: Si tú quieres ir para allá tienes que tomar un autobus.
definitions.en: If you want to get there, you will have to take a bus.

definitions.def: A pick-up truck, typically an old Toyota Tacoma, that goes around neighborhoods selling fruits and vegetables, often announcing their products with a megaphone.
definitions.ex: Si pasa una guagua platanera, párala pa' comprar fruta' pa' hacer una batida.
definitions.gs: Si pasa una guagua platanera, párala para comprar frutas para hacer un batido.
definitions.en: If a guagua platanera passes by, please stop it so I can buy some fruits for a smoothie.

definitions.gs: Tira eso en el bote de basura.

definitions.ex: Después que compraste ese carro tú ta' muy agentao.
definitions.gs: Después que compraste ese carro, tú estás muy arrogante.
definitions.en: You became very arrogant after you bought that car.

definitions.note: This term is ambiguous, as it can also mean "cookie". Context is key.
definitions.en: Do you want me to slap you?

definitions.note: This is the standard Spanish meaning. The Dominican usage as "slap" creates ambiguity.

definitions.def: A foreigner who knows a lot about Dominican culture.
definitions.ex: Ella es de Francia, pero ella ta' aplataná.
definitions.gs: Ella es de Francia, pero ella sabe mucho de la cultura dominicana.
definitions.en: She is from France, but she knows a lot about Dominican culture.

definitions.note: ‘Alalgalto’ used in the East region. ‘Alaigaito’ used in the North region.
From the English phrase "full jean," used by U.S. Marines in 1916 to describe the appearance of Dominican women in tight jeans.
definitions.en: You have dirt on your butt.

term: Ustedes son cagao / Ustedes son pin pun / Ustedes son dos gotas de agua

definitions.ex: ¿Él es hermano tuyo? Porque ustedes son cagao.
definitions.gs: ¿Él es tu hermano? Porque ustedes son idénticos.
definitions.en: Is he your brother? Because you two look a lot alike.

definitions.def: There is something wrong; this is suspicious.
definitions.ex: Aquí como que hay un maco.
definitions.en: There is something wrong here / There is something suspicious about this.

definitions.ex: Yo estoy a punto de coger el monte.

definitions.def: To not have problems with someone; to be on good terms with someone; to be cool with someone.
definitions.ex: Yo toy frio con mi suegra.
definitions.gs: Tengo una buena relación con mi suegra.
definitions.en: I am cool with my mother-in-law.

definitions.def: You are not street smart; you are lame; you don't have the guts to do it.
definitions.ex: Él no e' arretao pa' hacerlo, él no corre' a na'.
definitions.gs: Él no es lo suficientemente valiente para hacerlo.
definitions.en: He is not brave enough; he doesn't have the guts to do it.

definitions.def: Party watcher; a coward; a boring, slow person with no attitude.
definitions.ex: Si ella te guta, ve y habla con ella, no sea' pariguayo.
definitions.gs: Si a ella le gustas, ve y habla con ella, no seas soso.
definitions.en: If you like her, go and talk to her, don't be a coward.

definitions.def: Party watcher; a coward; a boring, slow person with no attitude.
An exclamation of surprise, anger, or emphasis, similar to "damn" or "fuck".
A minced oath for "Coño", similar to "Dang it".
